bzh.plealog.bioinfo.api.data.feature

Interface FeatureTable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cloneable, Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IFeatureTable

    public interface FeatureTable
extends Cloneable, Serializable
    This class defines a feature table associated to a sequence. As the name implied, a Feature Table is made of Features. However, it is also possible to associated to a Feature Table some values representing the origin of the data. These values are: Source, Message, Date and Status.
    Author:
    Patrick G. Durand

      • addFeature

        Feature addFeature(String key,
                 int from,
                 int to,
                 int strand)
        Adds a new feature within this table of features.
        Parameters:
        key - the key name of the feature
        from - starting position of the feature on the sequence (use zero-based value)
        to - ending position of the feature on the sequence (use zero-based value)
        strand - strand location of the feature on the sequence (use one of the Feature.xxxSTRAND constants)
        Returns:
        a newly created Feature

      • cut

        FeatureTable cut(int from,
               int to)
        Cut a feature table given new from and to values. Given from and to values, all features located outside the range are discarded, all features located fully within the range are conserved, as well as all features spanning from and/or to values. For the latter case, feature's coordinates are updated to fit within the range. Please provide a from value always less than to value. If the feature table is out of range given the new coordinates, then this method return null.
